{{Refimprove|date=October 2006}}
The '''New Orleans Zen Temple''' is a dojo of the [[Soto Zen]] tradition in [[New Orleans]], [[Louisiana]].  Robert Livingston Roshi was the abbot until his retirement in 2016, and Richard Collins is the current abbot.  Livingston, a close disciple of Taisen Deshimaru,  founded the temple in 1984.  Before his death in 1982, Deshimaru asked Livingston to go to the United States to open a Zen dojo and teach true Zen practice in the United States. The temple is also the home of the [http://www.nozt.org/aza.shtml American Zen Association], which gives support to zen dojos and publishes rare [[Buddhist]] texts.

